<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="84" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,969]" pageId="3" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,763,789]" pageId="3" pageNumber="84">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name of this new species is named for morphology of male cercus, from Latin ‘ 
<emphasis box="[1272,1316,763,788]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="84">arct</emphasis>
-’ (narrow) and ‘ 
<emphasis box="[208,272,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="84">lamin</emphasis>
-’ (lamellar).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="84" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,969]" pageId="3" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,834,860]" pageId="3" pageNumber="84">Discussion.</emphasis>
The new species resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="(Uvarov, 1933)" baseAuthorityName="Uvarov" baseAuthorityYear="1933" box="[650,1075,835,861]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Microconema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clavata">
<emphasis box="[650,894,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="84">Microconema clavata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Uvarov, B. P." box="[909,1066,835,861]" pageId="3" pageNumber="84" pagination="1 - 8" refId="ref2580" refString="Uvarov, B. P. (1933) Schwedisch-chinesische wissenschaftliche Expedition nach den nordwestlichen Provinzen Chinas. 6. Orthoptera. 5. Tettigoniidae. Arkiv for Zoologi, 26 A (1), 1 - 8." type="journal article" year="1933">Uvarov, 1933</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, but it differs from the latter in: male cercus on inner basal area with a narrow lamellar extension on dorsal margin and ventral margin respectively; subgenital plate nearly rectangular, with a median longitudinal furrow distinctly. Ventral margin of ovipositor with some small blunt teeth in subapical area.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
